			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>OK, I am not sure I follow what the last poster said. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>According to what I think, there will be no bobbing up and down (while idle, because while moving, ive never really noticed any bobbing). I do not see any change whatsoever in functionality :</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>- You will still be able to scale up a wall just like you can now, levi or not</DIV>
<DIV>- You will still be able to levitate, meaning you still be able to cross over the castle wall in Pofire</DIV>
<DIV>- You will not sink more because of the change</DIV>
<DIV>- You will not get stuck on rocks (in 99% of cases- to not say 100% -&nbsp;you will slide over the rock, just like you can scale a wall)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I believe the change is :</DIV>
<DIV>- In some select places, the bobbing is needed to access an area. Grumbuk aludes to the ledge in Chardok. If you scale the wall, and cross, without the bobbing you may be short on height, but with bobbing there is an instant where you will be high enough to cross. Personally, I am not sure bobbing is truly needed for that place, but I agree it helps make the crossing easier.</DIV>
<DIV>- In that special case, you can hit the jump key as you get near the ledge, to get the equivalent of the bobbing height change.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I believe no one needs to even know about the Jump key change for Levi to work as intended 99.9% of the time. For the rest, then ull need to know. But really, how often will you really need the jump key? I believe virtually never.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bluetiger</DIV>
																		
